According to statistics, between 30% and 75% of the drivers reported more than once for drunk driving then return to driving the car.
Alcohol would avoid it, because it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures the alcohol rate in the breathed air and prevents the car from being driven if the driver does not blow, or when a concentration of alcohol higher than the permitted one is detected.
The cost is more than EUR 1000 and would be borne by the sanctioned person.
In this regard, a study conducted in the United States in 2007 has shown that vehicles equipped with such devices can reduce up to 65% of the infringements committed during the first year of introduction.
