The prices of domestic industrial sales in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared with the previous month of 12.9% compared to August 2007 - reports the Central Institute of Hungarian Statistics.
The export sales prices of the industry reported in July 2008 were higher than 1.1%, compared to the previous year, decreased by 3.9%.
As a result of the variation in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were higher than 0.7% compared to the previous month and 3.2% compared to a year ago.
The prices of domestic industrial sales reported last month only increased by 0.1%.
The prices of domestic sales in the processing sector also rose to a minimum of 0.1% compared to July.
The increase in prices in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoe processing sector (2.8%), especially the bags and belts with 4.6% and the production of shoes with 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price level of plastic and chemical raw materials resulted in a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the chemicals and products sector.
A reduction in prices occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum extent in the processing of wood (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, publishing and typographic activities have not changed.
In the other sectors of the processing industry there has been an increase in prices between 0.2 and 0.9%.
In the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector prices increased by 0.3% in August in domestic industrial sales, primarily as a result of the dominant effect of the increase in the price of gas by the authorities since 1 July.
Compared to 12 months, in view of the domestic sales of the processing industry, the largest increases in the oil processing sector (32.4%).
In the field of the manufacture of products resulting from metal processing the price increase was 13.2%, 11% in the production of food, beverages and tobacco representing a determining weight.
A decrease in prices occurred in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.3%).
In the other sectors of the processing industry the rate of price increase varied from 0.6% to 9.1%.
Total prices in the processing industry over the past year rose by 10.2%.
The prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector exceeded 18.7% of last year's prices.
In domestic sales among target groups in the sectors, the biggest increase in monthly prices occurred in August in sectors producing investment goods (0.7%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods prices rose by 0.3%, in the energy and subsequent use sectors prices did not change compared to those of the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to last year's same month, the increase in higher prices was observed in the energy and subsequent use sector (16.8%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods the increase was 6.8%, for investment goods a decrease of 1.4% was measured.
The prices of industrial export sales calculated in guilders increased in August 1.1% compared to the previous month, compared with 12 months decreased by 3.9%.
