Brussels had asked the independent Scientific Committee to examine the problem, given the large use of portable musical devices and the increase in the number of young people exposed to the noise caused by them.
"Scientists - the EU executive concludes - confirm that there is cause for concern and the European Commission will now examine together with the Member States and stakeholders what measures could possibly be taken to better protect children and adolescents from exposure to noise from portable musical devices and related equipment."
